This is a thin adapter, not the canonical source (CLAUDE.md "M1-1"). The
canonical, vendor-neutral repository instructions — quick-reference commands,
the `scripts/verify.py` verification contract, architecture map, ChangeKind
conventions, test-quality gates, and the full "what NOT to do" list — live in
`/AGENTS.md`. Read that file before making a change.

Minimum before proposing a change is done:

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
python scripts/verify.py --profile pr   # == `pixi run check`; the real PR gate
```

Do not duplicate commands, invariants, or counts from `AGENTS.md` here — if
this file and `AGENTS.md` disagree, `AGENTS.md` is correct.
